http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Other-decisions/article13998374.ece

Allowing the syndicate members to ask ten questions and propose four resolutions in the meeting, nominating six meritorious students to the academic council of the university, recording of the discussion during the zero hour of the syndicate meeting, giving a grant of Rs. 1 lakh to ‘Sahitya Sambhrama’ literary fest being held on the university campus in Dharwad were some of other decisions taken during the syndicate meeting of Karnatak University, Dharwad, held on Tuesday, sources said. In the meeting chaired by Vice-Chancellor Pramod Gai it was also decided to appoint M. Gangadharappa as the chairman of the Community Radio Establishment Committee and appoint an officer for Public Relations and Media relations for the university.